# Changelog and versioning

Keep `CHANGELOG.md` and `package.json` version in sync. Update both after **every completed part** of work (feature slice, adapter, fix batch, docs milestone) — not only at release time.

## CHANGELOG rules

- File: `CHANGELOG.md` at repo root (create it when implementation starts).
- Format: [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/) sections: `Added`, `Changed`, `Deprecated`, `Removed`, `Fixed`, `Security`.
- **No dates** — do not use `## [1.2.0] - 2026-05-25` or any date lines.
- **Versions only** — use `## [1.2.0]` headers, newest version first.
- **Detailed entries** — each bullet explains *what* changed and *why it matters*, not one-word summaries.

```
# BAD
## [0.2.0] - 2026-05-25
- fixes

# GOOD
## [0.2.0]

### Added
- Anthropic Messages adapter: maps content_block_delta and tool_use streams
  to unified tool_call events, including index-to-id reconciliation when
  the provider sends id late.

### Fixed
- SSE parser no longer drops payloads when a chunk boundary splits mid-line.
```

## Versioning rules

- Follow [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/): `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`.
- Bump **PATCH** for fixes and small internal changes.
- Bump **MINOR** for new adapters, APIs, or backward-compatible features.
- Bump **MAJOR** only for breaking public API changes.
- Update `package.json` `"version"` to match the new CHANGELOG header in the **same commit** as the CHANGELOG update.
- Pre-1.0: `0.x.y` is fine; still bump after each completed part.

## When to update

After each logical deliverable, before moving on:

1. Add entries under the appropriate `## [x.y.z]` section (create the section if needed).
2. Bump `package.json` version to match.
3. Include CHANGELOG + version bump in the same commit as the code change, or immediately follow with a dedicated commit — never leave them stale across sessions.

## Unreleased work

If a part is incomplete, do not add a version header for it. Land CHANGELOG + version bump only when that part is done and tested.
